comments: Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) brings two hands to the ball to gather on his left foot and takes a legal two steps before releasing his shot.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) slightly extends his leg out after the release on his jump shot attempt and any follow-through contact with Holiday (MIL) is deemed marginal.
Connaughton (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact from Dort as he engages on the pick.

Holiday (MIL) makes marginal contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) face when his arm is extended.   Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Connaughton (MIL) makes clean ball contact to tie it up with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and a jump ball is correctly whistled.
Holiday (MIL) reaches for the ball and incidental follow-through contact occurs with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm after he tips the jump ball.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) is in the paint for around three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Dort (OKC) avoids making contact with Middleton's (MIL) arm during his shooting motion on the jump shot attempt.
Giddey (OKC) is progressing when he receives the pass and gathers on his right foot while establishing his left as his pivot, which he maintains prior to releasing his dribble.
Holiday (MIL) makes incidental high-five contact with Giddey's (OKC) hand after he releases his pass.
Giddey (OKC) releases the inbounds pass within 5 seconds.
Connaughton (MIL) cleanly deflects the pass and is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Holiday (MIL) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs as they use the screen during the inbound.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) gathers the rebound on his right foot and establishes his left as his pivot. He releases his dribble before lifting his left foot.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) come together and incidental contact occurs as they both pursue the rebound.
Bazley (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position on Antetokounmpo (MIL) during the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Middleton (MIL) and Dort (OKC) engage and disengage off-ball and the contact is marginal as it does not affect Dort's ability to receive the inbounds pass.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Holiday's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact on the screen.
Dort (OKC) clamps and holds Middleton's (MIL) left arm, which affects his ability to get to the inbounds pass.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) dislodges the rebound from Antetokounmpo (MIL) and is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.

comments: The ball touches Middleton's (MIL) body last before rolling out of bounds.

Before the block, Antetokounmpo (MIL) makes contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) face and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) commits a take foul on Antetokounmpo (MIL).
